Results.ReviewText: I have been using Nescafé Gold Blend for at least as many years as it has been presented in its distinctively curved jar. With regard to the actual coffee blend, as far as I can tell, there is no difference in taste. I believe the jar shape is the only thing to have changed and I would hazard a guess that the change was made for reasons of cheaper production, lighter weight of glass and the ability to ship more jars per lorry load. Although I generally like the taste of Nescafé Gold Blend I have found that there can occasionally be some variation in intensity of taste between one jar and another, some seeming particularly bland and requiring two teaspoons per cup to achieve the same taste experience.
Results.Title: New Packaging

Results.ReviewText: We ususally buy the Nescafe Classic Instant but the store we were at never had any. So we decided to Gold Blend Instant. At first I was a little put out that the store never had any Classic. But once I had a cup of Gold Blend I realised that the store not having any Classsic actually done me a favour. A great cup of coffee, great flavour and beats any of those home coffee machines about these days. Its my go to coffee now every morning and afternoon. I recently introduced other family members and friends to Gold Blend and they all agree its a great cup of coffee. Highly recommend!
Results.Title: A Great Cup of Coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: There are so many different and eye-catching offers in supermarkets these days as well as so many new, exciting products to try. However, there's one product that I buy without deviation again and again - Nescafé Gold Blend. I have been drinking it for years and it's the first thing I have in the morning and my evening milky drink, too. Its rich aroma and smooth taste make it perfect at any time of the day, whatever the occasion. I've also used it in baking and cooking, too and the flavour never disappoints. An all-round, gorgeous coffee blend.
Results.Title: Simply the best!

Results.ReviewText: Earlier this year I purchased Gold Blend for the first time because it was on offer in my supermarket and I was instantly hooked by its smooth yet full-flavour taste.  I used to only ever purchase Nescafe Original because it has a robust coffee taste but it could be a little sharp if I made it too strong. Not so with Gold Blend.This is a rich tasting coffee that remains smooth and tasty no matter how strong I make it. Whether you make it with water or milk, the taste comes through and is extremely more-ish. Be warned though....one cup is never enough! This is the perfect larder coffee since it is  an all-rounder for the entire family and, of course, friends. Try and and you won't go back to your previous brand.
Results.Title: The gold standard of instant coffee

Results.ReviewText: Hi Nescafe, Well I usually have the Nescafe 3-in-1 coffee sachets but as I am now 'single use plastic aware' I have changed my ways of buying coffee! I don't like much milk but I do have sugar. I bought a jar of Nescafe Rich & Smooth and am so pleased with the taste, texture & strength that I will be sticking with buying this coffee in a jar! I like to taste my coffee (rich) but as I don't have much milk it needs to be smooth and with a touch of sugar it makes 'my perfect coffee' every time. I would definitely recommend it as a good priced, good tasting and smooth coffee.

Results.ReviewText:
My wife and I have been Gold Blend devotees for many years but the new recipe has changed that. Why Nescafe have taken it upon themselves to change a tried and tested product is beyond me. The new recipe has microgrounds added but for me they add nothing to the taste which is very bland compared to the previous recipe. I have read that the intention is to provide more of a "Barista style" coffee but Nescafe already provide such a blend for those who choose it. I feel it is misleading not to highlight that there is a new recipe and 'original' should not be applied in any way.
I would also add that the new jars do not provide enough distinction between the varieties and we accidentally bought a jar of decaff. The tops are now all the same colour and the labels very similar.
I am pleased to say that we have found another product that is far superior and have switched to that.
Results.Title: Bye Bye Nescafe it was nice knowing you
